  "prompt": "What is the limit to follow in Instagram?",
  "response": "Instagram has several limits and guidelines to ensure a positive user experience and prevent spam or abuse. Here are some key limits to be aware of:\n\n### **Follow Limits**\n1. **Daily Follow Limit**: You can follow up to **200 accounts per day** on Instagram. Exceeding this limit may result in temporary restrictions.\n2. **Total Follow Limit**: You can follow up to **7,500 accounts** in total. If you reach this limit, you\u2019ll need to unfollow some accounts before following new ones.\n\n### **Like, Comment, and Messaging Limits**\n3. **Likes**: There is no official daily like limit, but excessive liking in a short period (e.g., hundreds per hour) may trigger Instagram\u2019s spam detection.\n4. **Comments**: You can leave up to **50-100 comments per hour**, depending on your account\u2019s activity level.\n5. **DMs (Direct Messages)**: Limit of **30-50 DMs per hour** to avoid being flagged as spam.\n\n### **Posting Limits**\n6. **Posts**: There\u2019s no specific limit on the number of posts per day, but posting too frequently (e.g., dozens of posts in a few hours) may be flagged as spam.\n7. **Stories**: You can post up to **100 stories per day**, but this is not recommended as it may overwhelm your followers.\n\n### **Other Limits**\n8. **Unfollow Limits**: Limit of **200 unfollows per day** to avoid being flagged for suspicious activity.\n9. **Hashtags**: Use up to **30 hashtags per post** or **10 hashtags for Stories**. Exceeding this won\u2019t show additional tags.\n\n### **Important Notes**\n- These limits may vary slightly depending on your account\u2019s age, activity level, and history.\n- Repeatedly exceeding these limits may result in temporary blocks, shadowbans, or account suspension.\n- Instagram\u2019s algorithms are designed to detect and reduce spammy behavior, so it\u2019s best to engage naturally and avoid automation tools.\n\nAlways refer to Instagram\u2019s **Community Guidelines** and **Terms of Use** for the most accurate and updated information.",
